==English==

===Intransitive verb===
'''[[break]] [[up]]'''
#To break or separate into pieces; to [[disintegrate]] or come apart.
#:''It '''broke up''' when it hit the ground.''
#{{idiom}} To end a [[relationship]].
#:''She '''broke up''' with her boyfriend last week.''
#{{idiom}} Of a telephone conversation, to cease to be understandable because of a bad connection.
#:''You are '''breaking up'''.  Can you repeat that?''

===Transitive verb===
'''break up'''
#To break or separate into pieces.
#:'''''Break up''' the cheese and put it in the salad.''
#{{idiom}} To [[stop]] a [[fight]]; to separate people who are fighting.
#:''The police came in to '''break up''' the disturbance.''

